climbs.name: Ruby on Rails
climbs.fa: Jon Brenner, but maybe climbed before

content.description: Scale the huge rails. It has a spicy, slopey, slabby topout.
content.location: It is on the North side of the boulder with the big ol' rails.

climbs.name: Python
climbs.fa: Jon Brenner, but maybe climbed before

content.description: Climb up the huge flake, then sliver and traverse your way across the ledge to meet up with the topout of Data Frames.
content.location: On the back (west) side of the boulder, find the huge ledge. This problem starts on the left side of the ledge.

content.description: Sit start the arete, move up, and top out.
content.location: This ascends the right arete on the backside of the boulder.

content.description: Climb the south face. Avoid the huge, metal nails.
content.location: On the South face with the 3 pine trees, stick to the right side.

content.description: Find a right hand undercling at about chest level and a decent crimpy pinch hold at about head height for your left hand. Find good low feet, and make a couple moves to a great right hand rail. Work your way up and over the bulge to some scary slab moves, and top out. NOTE - the right hand undercling start feels like it could break off at some point!
content.location: It is on the backside of the boulder at the far left side of the slightly overhanging face.

content.description: Crouch start the steep nose/arete, make some burly moves, and top out.
content.location: This ascends the steep nose/arete on the right side of the boulder as you enter the parking lot.

content.description: Analogic Boulder is a big block in the middle of a parking lot. It is very hard to access with security and employees always around.
